com.quest.glue.api.services
Interface WMIResultSet2

All Superinterfaces:
java.io.Closeable, java.lang.Iterable<WMIObject>
public interface WMIResultSet2
extends java.lang.Iterable<WMIObject>, java.io.Closeable

Contains the results of a query executed by WMIConnection. The Connection interface can be safely accessed through multiple threads. Queries executed on it will return an concrete implementation of this interface to access the results.

This updated result set interface continues to support the previous while ( next() ) {} style of iteration. This method modifies the internal state of the result set and is therefore inherently not thread safe. It also has the limitation of allowing only a single pass through the generated results. Once the iteration has finished the result set should be immediately closed.

This result set also supports the Iterable interface so that it can be used as the target of foreach statements. Combined with the WMIObject interface this allows the results of queries to be iterated over more naturally. Because this method does not modify the internal state of the result set it is safe to use with multiple threads and allows the results to be iterated over more than once. 

 WMIResultSet2 results = mConnection.executeQuery( "SELECT a, b FROM Some_Things" );
 try {
     for ( WMIObject result : results ) {
         // work with this object
     }
 }
 finally {
     mConnection.close( results );
 }

This

The API provided by WMIResultSet has been maintained and expanded to support objects, references, and arrays of strings, numbers, WMIObjects, and WMIReferences so that WMIResultSet2 can be used as a drop-in replacement for existing code that needs to access these new attributes.

Since:
5.5.5.4

Method Detail

close

void close()
Immediately closes this result set. Any resources used by the results will be freed eventually by the garbage collector, but users are encouraged to manually close results as soon as they are no longer needed to release any connections and other resources immediately.

Specified by:
close in interface java.io.Closeable

executeMethod

java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> executeMethod(java.lang.String methodName,
                                                               java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> methodParameters)
                                                               throws java.io.IOException
Execute a method on the currently selected WMI object. Once the method has been executed any values it returns will be read and returned in a single shot. Although this will commonly end up returning values that may not be used by clients it is more effecient to grab them all at once than even one or two individually.

Not all methods require parameters. Passing null or an empty set for methodParameters is acceptable.

Parameters:
methodName - The name of the method to invoke on the currently selected object
methodParameters - The name->value pairs for parameters included in the method call or null
Returns:
The name->value mapping of all the values returned by this method
Throws:
java.io.IOException - The method call was not completed successfully

next

boolean next()
             throws java.io.IOException
Return the next item in the current result set. If there are no more rows to return this will return false, otherwise it will return true and the contents of the row can be safely queried.

Returns:
True if a row was retreived
Throws:
java.io.IOException - The connection to the remote server was broken
